cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI 

This paper is about Learning-to-rank (LETOR) which is a popular technique in information retrieval, a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper proposes a novel neural architecture for LETOR, which involves modeling the context of a query. This involves techniques from machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR, followed by cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, and cs.AI.
